@chetan51 - When I first saw this I didn't realize the CELL_MAX, etc were used as defaults. I thought they were just used as bounds checks. So there are two issues:

1. Bounds checks. I don't see any theory reason to limit these but we get a hard limit from the number of bits we use. So if the parameter for number of cells is UInt16 then we are limited to ~16k cells. I think it would be simplest to set UInt32 for all three and not explicitly enforce a limit. You could set it lower (like 16 bit for segments and synapses) if you really want to restrict clients of the class but it makes sense to me to be more conservative on this.
2. Default values. Do we want a default number of cells? It seems to me that client code should be required to explicitly set this. But for the defaults we do set, it is hard to see what you are actually setting them to so I suggest just using integer literals:

```
static const MAX_SEGMENTS = 256;
static const MAX_SYNAPSES = 256;
```

