for now you can simply create your own selector class and pass it in:
```
class MySelector()
class MyRoundRobinSelector(ConnectionSelector):
    def __init__(self, opts):
        super(MyRoundRobinSelector, self).__init__(opts)
        self.data = threading.local()
        self.data.rr = -1

    def select(self, connections):
        self.data.rr += 1
        self.data.rr %= len(connections)
        return connections[self.data.rr]

es = Elasticsearch(selector_class=MyRoundRobinSelector)
```

or use `RandomSelector` as a workaround.

